    "type": "targeted_grid",
    "name": "threshold_144_narrow",
    "description": "Narrows the economic_split threshold for v27 victory in the 144-block retarget regime with the BASELINE (linear) price oracle.\nMOTIVATION: econ_switching_144_verify showed:\n  econ=0.20 \u2192 v26_dominant (v26 cascade at t=624s, 1846 v26 blocks, peak gap 45.5%)\n  econ=0.35 \u2192 v27_dominant (v27 cascade at t=1818s, 791 v26 blocks, peak gap 15.5%)\n\nThe threshold is bracketed at (0.20, 0.35). The analysis script estimated \u22480.387 but that's a linear interpolation artifact \u2014 the true boundary could be anywhere in (0.20, 0.35). This sweep probes four points to narrow it substantially.\nResearch question: Does the threshold fall near 0.22, 0.25, or 0.28?\nMECHANISM: In the 144-block regime both forks can hit their first retarget quickly. The fork that accumulates 144 blocks first gets a difficulty reduction, which makes it more profitable, triggering a cascade to that fork. The initial price gap determines which fork neutral pools prefer and therefore which one mines faster.\nPRICE GAP AT START (with 50/50 hashrate):\n  econ=0.22 \u2192 v26 premium \u2248 11.2%  (neutral pools strongly prefer v26)\n  econ=0.25 \u2192 v26 premium \u2248 8.0%   (moderate v26 preference)\n  econ=0.28 \u2192 v26 premium \u2248 5.6%   (weaker v26 preference)\n  econ=0.30 \u2192 v26 premium \u2248 3.6%   (slight v26 preference; may not overcome v27 ideology)\n\nCommitted v27 pool tolerance = 0.51 \u00d7 0.26 = 13.26%. The initial price gaps at econ=0.22 (11.2%) and 0.25 (8.0%) are below this tolerance, so committed v27 pools won't switch based on price alone. What drives the v26 win is the neutral bloc's 16% threshold \u2014 they switch EARLY to v26, letting v26 retarget first.\nEXPECTED OUTCOMES:\n  econ=0.22: likely v26_dominant (close to 0.20 which gave v26 win)\n  econ=0.25: uncertain \u2014 borderline; test is the main purpose\n  econ=0.28: likely v27_dominant (v26 premium insufficient to swing neutral bloc)\n  econ=0.30: v27_dominant (confirmed by proximity to econ=0.35)\n\nPRIOR RESULTS FOR CONTEXT:\n  econ=0.20 (144-block, baseline): v26_dominant, cascade t=624s, 1846 v26 blocks\n  econ=0.35 (144-block, baseline): v27_dominant, cascade t=1818s, 791 v26 blocks\n\nRun on a single namespace (4 runs \u00d7 4,000s = ~4.4h):\n\n  python 3_run_sweep.py \\\n    --input threshold_144_narrow/build_manifest.json \\\n    --namespace sweep-144-narrow \\\n    --results-dir threshold_144_narrow/results \\\n    --duration 4000 --retarget-interval 144 --interval 2\n\nNamespace to create first:\n  kubectl create namespace sweep-144-narrow\n\nWall-clock estimate: 4 \u00d7 4,000s = ~4.4h\n",
